msg19, ..., msg1]\n- messages.reverse() => [msg1, msg2, ..., msg20] (oldest firs
t)\n- nextCursor = hasMore && messages.length > 0 ? String(messages[0].sequence_
id) : null\n- messages[0].sequence_id = msg1.sequence_id = 1\n\nNext query: curs
or = 1, qb.andWhere("m.sequence_id < :cursor", { cursor: 1 })\nThis would get me
ssages with sequence_id < 1, which is nothing!\n\nThis is a **blocking bug**! Th
e nextCursor should be the sequence_id of the **first** message in the original 
