etCurrentConversation` is processed, the state might not be `MessagesLoaded` yet
.\n\nWait, in `ChatPage.initState()`:\n```dart\nbloc.add(ImSetCurrentConversatio
n(widget.conversationId));\nbloc.add(LoadMessages(conversationId: widget.convers
ationId));\n```\n\nBoth events are added to the event queue. `_onSetCurrentConve
rsation` runs first. At this point, the state is likely `ImInitial` (if first ti
me) or previous `MessagesLoaded` (if coming from another chat). If it\'s `ImInit
ial`, pending messages won\'t be merged. Then `LoadMessages` runs and emits `Mes
sagesLoaded`. But pending messages were NOT merged!\n\nThis is a race condition 
/ ordering issue. The pending messages should be merged during `LoadMessages`, n
ot just during `SetCurrentConversation`. Looking at `_onLoadMessages`, it DOES m
erge pending:\n```dart\n// Merge any pending messages for current conversation\n
if (_currentConversationId == event.conversationId &&\n    _pendingMessages.cont
ainsKey(event.conversationId)) {\n  final pending = _pendingMessages[event.conve
rsationId]!;\n  _pendingMessages.remove(event.conversationId);\n  ...\n  allMess
ages.addAll(uniquePending);\n}\n```\n\nSo pending messages ARE merged during `Lo
adMessages`. Good. The `ImSetCurrentConversation` handler is an extra merge for 
when you\'re already in a conversation and switch to it (e.g., from a notificati
