connectRequested` is called (e.g., on logout), it only transitions `MessagesLoad
ed` states:\n```dart\nif (state is MessagesLoaded) {\n  final currentState = sta
te as MessagesLoaded;\n  emit(MessagesLoaded(\n    messages: currentState.messag
es,\n    hasMore: currentState.hasMore,\n    nextCursor: currentState.nextCursor
,\n    isConnected: false,\n    ...\n  ));\n}\n```\n\nIf the state is `MessageSe
nding`, it does NOT transition. So the message is stuck in "sending". This is a 
bug.\n\nBut what about when the socket disconnects unexpectedly (not via `ImDisc
onnectRequested`)? The `ImSocketClient` has reconnection configured, but if reco
nnection fails after 5 attempts, the socket is dead. Does the BLoC know? Looking
at `ImSocketClient`, there\'s no `onDisconnect` callback passed to the BLoC! So 
the BLoC never knows when the socket disconnects unexpectedly.\n\nWait, looking 
at `ImSocketClient`:\n```dart\n_socket = io.io(namespaceUrl, <String, dynamic>{\
n  \'transports\': [\'websocket\'],\n  \'autoConnect\': true,\n  \'reconnection\
': true,\n  \'reconnectionAttempts\': 5,\n  \'reconnectionDelay\': 1000,\n  \'re
connectionDelayMax\': 5000,\n  \'auth\': <String, dynamic>{\'token\': token},\n}
);\n```\n\nThere are no `onConnect`, `onDisconnect`, `onReconnect`, `onReconnect
Error` callbacks. The BLoC has no way to know the socket connection state change
d except when it explicitly connects/disconnects. This means:\n1. If socket disc
onnects unexpectedly, BLoC still thinks `isConnected: true`\n2. If socket reconn
ects, BLoC doesn\'t know\n3. Messages sent during unexpected disconnect will be 
