off-by-one risk for empty results after cursor** - Actually I verified this is c
orrect. Let me not flag this.\n\nWait, let me reconsider. I want to be very care
ful about what I flag as Major vs Minor.\n\nActually, looking at the `im_bloc.da
rt` more carefully:\n\nIn `_onSendMessage`:\n```dart\nemit(MessageSending(\n    
messages: newMessages, clientMessageId: clientMessageId));\n\nif (_socketClient?
.isConnected ?? false) {\n  _socketClient!.sendMessage(...);\n} else {\n  final 
updatedMessages = newMessages.map((m) {\n    if (m.clientMessageId == clientMess
ageId) {\n      return m.copyWith(status: \'failed\');\n    }\n    return m;\n  
}).toList();\n  final prevState = state is MessagesLoaded ? state as MessagesLoa
ded : null;\n  emit(MessagesLoaded(\n    messages: updatedMessages,\n    hasMore
: prevState?.hasMore ?? false,\n    nextCursor: prevState?.nextCursor,\n    isCo
nnected: false,\n    ...\n  ));\n}\n```\n\nWhen socket is connected, message goe
s to `MessageSending`. If socket then disconnects unexpectedly:\n- `ImSocketClie
nt` doesn\'t notify BLoC\n- BLoC state remains `MessageSending`\n- The message s
tatus stays `sending` forever\n\nThis is a real bug. However, if the user sends 
another message, `_socketClient?.isConnected` would be false, so the new message
is marked `failed`. But the old message is still `sending`.\n\nAlso, looking at 
